<subSubSection id="EBF5653D9E57FF98FF2F7275FE5E1248" lastPageId="84" lastPageNumber="84" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A35036B69E57FF9FFF2F7275FC3E14EB" blockId="83.[128,654,1501,1759]" lastBlockId="83.[701,1228,213,945]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">
COMMENTS: Chapman gave the AMNH number of the 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E57FF9FFEE77295FE4C10E8" box="[340,442,1679,1701]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">holotype</typeStatus>
in the original description and said that he had four males, four females, and a young male (taken on 21 April). Only two males, two female plumaged birds, and the immature male were found in AMNH; the remaining 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E57FF9FFC60750AFBB21768" box="[979,1092,272,293]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">paratypes</typeStatus>
were probably among borrowed specimens. 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E57FF9FFBEA7534FB3A170E" box="[1113,1228,302,323]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Paratypes</typeStatus>
in AMNH: City of 
<collectingRegion id="612BF8549E57FF9FFC037551FBFC172C" box="[944,1034,331,353]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Mexico</collectingRegion>
, 
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E57FF9FFBA97551FB32172D" bold="true" box="[1050,1220,331,352]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">AMNH 41788</emphasis>
, adult male, 
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E57FF9FFCFE7572FC001730" bold="true" box="[845,1014,360,381]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">AMNH 41789</emphasis>
, female, undated, from the G.N. 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E57FF9FFC37759DFC0317D1" authority="LeCroy, 2013" authorityName="LeCroy" authorityYear="2013" box="[900,1013,391,412]" genus="Lawrence" pageId="83" pageNumber="136" rank="genus" status="G.N.">Lawrence</taxonomicName>
Collection, cataloged in 1889 and labeled 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E57FF9FFB9675BEFB6A17F4" baseAuthorityName="P.L.Statius Mueller" baseAuthorityYear="1776" box="[1061,1180,420,441]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Carpodacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E57FF9FFB9675BEFB6A17F4" box="[1061,1180,420,441]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Chapman; Las Vigas, 
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E57FF9FFC6775DBFB79179B" bold="true" box="[980,1167,449,470]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">AMNH 153359</emphasis>
, immature male, 
<date id="D75110769E57FF9FFCD375C5FBF517B9" box="[864,1027,479,501]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" value="1897-04-21">21 April 1897</date>
, 
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E57FF9FFBA375C5FB3217B9" bold="true" box="[1040,1220,479,500]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">AMNH 153360</emphasis>
, adult male, 
<date id="D75110769E57FF9FFCE275E7FC0A145F" box="[849,1020,508,530]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" value="1897-04-21">21 April 1897</date>
, 
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E57FF9FFBBF75E6FB32145C" bold="true" box="[1036,1220,508,529]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">AMNH 153361</emphasis>
, [female plumage], 
<date id="D75110769E57FF9FFC207600FBC01462" box="[915,1078,538,560]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" value="1897-04-24">24 April 1897</date>
, all collected by Chapman. These last three 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E57FF9FFB957622FB611400" box="[1062,1175,568,589]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">paratypes</typeStatus>
and the 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E57FF9FFD42764FFCA11426" box="[753,855,597,619]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">holotype</typeStatus>
represent the four specimens that 
<bibRefCitation id="C77E4B479E57FF9FFD4B7669FC1914C4" author="Chapman, F. M." box="[760,1007,627,649]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" pagination="15 - 43" refId="ref114197" refString="Chapman, F. M. 1898. Notes on birds observed at Jalapa and Las Vigas, Vera Cruz, Mexico. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 10 (2), 15 - 43, pl. 3." type="journal article" year="1898">Chapman (1898: 42)</bibRefCitation>
later said that he collected at Las Vigas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A35036B69E57FF9FFD6876B5FBC015FC" blockId="83.[701,1228,213,945]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">
<bibRefCitation id="C77E4B479E57FF9FFD6876B5FC0D1488" author="Grinnell, J." box="[731,1019,687,709]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" pagination="17 - 22" refId="ref117074" refString="Grinnell, J. 1917. The subspecies of Hesperiphona vespertina. Condor 19: 17 - 22." type="journal article" year="1917">Grinnell (1917: 17–22)</bibRefCitation>
, in a study of 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E57FF9FFD0E76D6FC2214AF" baseAuthorityName="W.Cooper" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[701,980,716,739]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Hesperiphona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vespertina">
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E57FF9FFD0E76D6FC2214AF" box="[701,980,716,739]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Hesperiphona vespertina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
showed that USNM 35150 from Mirador, Vera Cruz, 
<collectingCountry id="DBF876269E57FF9FFBDE76F0FB31154D" box="[1133,1223,746,768]" name="Mexico" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, should be considered the 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E57FF9FFBA67712FBB11550" box="[1045,1095,776,797]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E57FF9FFB347712FC641576" authority="Ridgway" authorityName="Ridgway" authorityYear="1874" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Hesperiphona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" species="vespertina" variety="montana">
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E57FF9FFB347712FCD61576" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">H. v. montana</emphasis>
Ridgway
</taxonomicName>
and that, therefore, 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E57FF9FFB3C773CFCC21515" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Coccothraustes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" species="vespertinus" variety="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E57FF9FFB3C773CFCC21515" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">H. v. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
became a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E57FF9FFBDA7759FC45153B" authority="(Grinnell, 1917: 18)" baseAuthorityName="Grinnell" baseAuthorityPageNumber="18" baseAuthorityYear="1917" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Paroreomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E57FF9FFBDA7759FB3D1515" box="[1129,1227,835,856]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">montana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C77E4B479E57FF9FFD76777AFC5F153B" author="Grinnell, J." box="[709,937,864,886]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" pagination="17 - 22" refId="ref117074" refString="Grinnell, J. 1917. The subspecies of Hesperiphona vespertina. Condor 19: 17 - 22." type="journal article" year="1917">Grinnell, 1917: 18</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="C77E4B479E57FF9FFC75777AFB3D153B" author="Hellmayr, C. E." box="[966,1227,864,886]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" refId="ref119675" refString="Hellmayr, C. E. 1938. Catalogue of birds of the Americas and the adjacent islands. Ploceidae - Catamblyrhynchidae - Fringillidae. Chicago: Field Museum of Natural History, Publication 430, Zoological Series, vol. 13, Part 11, vi + 662 pp." type="book" year="1938">Hellmayr (1938: 148)</bibRefCitation>
agreed with this conclusion as did 
<bibRefCitation id="C77E4B479E57FF9FFBDB7764FC8F15FC" author="Deignan, H. G." pageId="83" pageNumber="83" refId="ref115430" refString="Deignan, H. G. 1961. Type specimens of birds in the United States National Museum. United States National Museum Bulletin 221: x + 718 pp." type="book" year="1961">Deignan (1961: 606–607)</bibRefCitation>
; also see below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A35036B69E57FF9FFD7077CFFC0C1245" blockId="83.[707,1222,980,1032]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">
[
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E57FF9FFD7977CEFB3415A7" authority="Mearns" authorityName="Mearns" box="[714,1218,980,1003]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Coccothraustes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="vespertina" subSpecies="montana">
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E57FF9FFD7977CEFBA815A7" box="[714,1118,980,1003]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Coccothraustes vespertina montana</emphasis>
Mearns
</taxonomicName>
, ex Ridg.]
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A35036B69E57FF9FFD68703AFBCB1007" blockId="83.[701,1228,1056,1759]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">
The two specimens bearing AMNH 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E57FF9FFB29703AFB3A1278" box="[1178,1228,1056,1077]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">type</typeStatus>
labels and marked as above, AMNH 52480 and AMNH 52490, have no standing as 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E57FF9FFB3B7046FB3E123C" box="[1160,1224,1116,1137]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">types</typeStatus>
. The 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E57FF9FFD417063FCD212C3" box="[754,804,1145,1166]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E57FF9FFCFF7062FC9912E6" authority="Ridgway, 1874" authorityName="Ridgway" authorityYear="1874" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Hesperiphona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="vespertina" subSpecies="montana">
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E57FF9FFCFF7062FB3D12C3" box="[844,1227,1144,1167]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Hesperiphona vespertina montana</emphasis>
Ridgway, 1874
</taxonomicName>
, is in USNM (
<bibRefCitation id="C77E4B479E57FF9FFBAF708CFCF31284" author="Grinnell, J." pageId="83" pageNumber="83" pagination="17 - 22" refId="ref117074" refString="Grinnell, J. 1917. The subspecies of Hesperiphona vespertina. Condor 19: 17 - 22." type="journal article" year="1917">Grinnell, 1917: 17–22</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="C77E4B479E57FF9FFCAF70AEFBA61287" author="Deignan, H. G." box="[796,1104,1204,1226]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" refId="ref115430" refString="Deignan, H. G. 1961. Type specimens of birds in the United States National Museum. United States National Museum Bulletin 221: x + 718 pp." type="book" year="1961">Deignan, 1961: 606–607</bibRefCitation>
). AMNH 52480 is a female, collected at Fort Verde, 
<collectingRegion id="612BF8549E57FF9FFD0E70F5FCE91348" box="[701,799,1263,1285]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Arizona</collectingRegion>
, on 
<date id="D75110769E57FF9FFCD770F5FBC61348" box="[868,1072,1263,1285]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" value="1885-08-14">14 August 1885</date>
, by Mearns (no. 4163), long after Ridgway’s description in 1874, and is his ‘‘type’’ of the adult female (
<bibRefCitation id="C77E4B479E57FF9FFD767152FC691313" author="Mearns, E. A." box="[709,927,1352,1374]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" pagination="243 - 251" refId="ref123262" refString="Mearns, E. A. 1890. Descriptions of a new species and three new subspecies of birds from Arizona. Auk 7: 243 - 251." type="journal article" year="1890">Mearns, 1890: 247</bibRefCitation>
). AMNH 52490 is a male, collected at Oak Creek, near Fort Verde, 
<collectingRegion id="612BF8549E57FF9FFD0E7199FCE913D4" box="[701,799,1411,1433]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Arizona</collectingRegion>
, on 
<date id="D75110769E57FF9FFCD77199FBC613D4" box="[868,1072,1411,1433]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" value="1885-08-14">14 August 1885</date>
, by Mearns (no. 4165) and is discussed as a young male in first plumage (
<bibRefCitation id="C77E4B479E57FF9FFCC371A4FBA01399" author="Mearns, E. A." box="[880,1110,1470,1492]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" pagination="243 - 251" refId="ref123262" refString="Mearns, E. A. 1890. Descriptions of a new species and three new subspecies of birds from Arizona. Auk 7: 243 - 251." type="journal article" year="1890">Mearns, 1890: 248</bibRefCitation>
). Because they have long been in the 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E57FF9FFBB271C6FBC513BC" box="[1025,1075,1500,1521]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">type</typeStatus>
collection at AMNH with 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E57FF9FFCD671E0FC611042" box="[869,919,1530,1551]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">type</typeStatus>
labels, they remain there with an additional label to explain that they have no nomenclatural standing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A35036B69E57FF98FD687249FE79151E" blockId="83.[701,1228,1056,1759]" lastBlockId="84.[93,620,213,851]" lastPageId="84" lastPageNumber="84" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">
<bibRefCitation id="C77E4B479E57FF9FFD687249FBE21024" author="Deignan, H. G." box="[731,1044,1619,1641]" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" refId="ref115430" refString="Deignan, H. G. 1961. Type specimens of birds in the United States National Museum. United States National Museum Bulletin 221: x + 718 pp." type="book" year="1961">Deignan (1961: 606–607)</bibRefCitation>
discussed the Ridgway type of 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E57FF9FFC22726BFC0210CB" baseAuthorityName="Grinnell" baseAuthorityYear="1917" box="[913,1012,1649,1670]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Paroreomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E57FF9FFC22726BFC0210CB" box="[913,1012,1649,1670]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in USNM. Ridgway did not specifically designate a type when he named the form. 
<bibRefCitation id="C77E4B479E57FF9FFC5F72B1FD171092" author="Grinnell, J." pageId="83" pageNumber="83" pagination="17 - 22" refId="ref117074" refString="Grinnell, J. 1917. The subspecies of Hesperiphona vespertina. Condor 19: 17 - 22." type="journal article" year="1917">Grinnell (1917: 18– 19)</bibRefCitation>
explained in detail why he considered USNM 35150 from near Mirador, near Vera Cruz, 
<collectingCountry id="DBF876269E50FF98FF1674E8FF091745" box="[165,255,242,264]" name="Mexico" pageId="84" pageNumber="84">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, to be the type of 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E50FF98FE6674E9FDC11745" baseAuthorityName="Grinnell" baseAuthorityYear="1917" box="[469,567,243,264]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Paroreomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="84" pageNumber="84" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E50FF98FE6674E9FDC11745" box="[469,567,243,264]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="84">montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and so indicated in the original description (also, see above). 
<bibRefCitation id="C77E4B479E50FF98FF497537FE03170E" author="Zimmer, J. T." box="[250,501,301,323]" pageId="84" pageNumber="84" pagination="213" refId="ref131496" refString="Zimmer, J. T. 1953. The original decription of Hesperiphona vespertina montana Ridgway. Auk 70: 213." type="journal article" year="1953">Zimmer (1953: 213)</bibRefCitation>
accepted Grinnell’s explanation and added relevant details. Deignan accepted USNM 35150 as the type. But he adds: ‘‘Despite all this, the label of a skin from Cantonment Burgwyn, New 
<collectingRegion id="612BF8549E50FF98FF1175DAFF0F179B" box="[162,249,448,470]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="84" pageNumber="84">Mexico</collectingRegion>
(No. 11960), is the one that bears the words ‘Type of supposed ‘var. montana’–RR.’’ It is this specimen that 
<bibRefCitation id="C77E4B479E50FF98FFEE7602FEBF1463" author="Mearns, E. A." box="[93,329,536,558]" pageId="84" pageNumber="84" pagination="243 - 251" refId="ref123262" refString="Mearns, E. A. 1890. Descriptions of a new species and three new subspecies of birds from Arizona. Auk 7: 243 - 251." type="journal article" year="1890">Mearns (1890: 247)</bibRefCitation>
listed as the ‘‘type’’ of the adult male, USNM 11960, collected at Cantonment Burgwyn, New 
<collectingRegion id="612BF8549E50FF98FE707649FDEB1424" box="[451,541,595,617]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="84" pageNumber="84">Mexico</collectingRegion>
, on 
<date id="D75110769E50FF98FDEE7649FF2C14CB" pageId="84" pageNumber="84" value="1859-06-03">3 June 1859</date>
, by W.W. Anderson, and noted that it was indistinguishable from nominate 
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E50FF98FFEE76B1FF21148D" box="[93,215,683,704]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E50FF98FFEE76B1FF25148D" baseAuthorityName="W.Cooper" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[93,211,683,704]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Hesperiphona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="84" pageNumber="84" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vespertina">vespertina</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
I do not consider that Mearns, by listing this specimen as the ‘‘type’’ of the male of 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E50FF98FFCD76FCFF1714B6" baseAuthorityName="Grinnell" baseAuthorityYear="1917" box="[126,225,742,763]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Paroreomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="84" pageNumber="84" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E50FF98FFCD76FCFF1714B6" box="[126,225,742,763]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="84">montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
designated it the 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E50FF98FE0776FFFDEB14B6" box="[436,541,741,763]" pageId="84" pageNumber="84">lectotype</typeStatus>
of the name 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E50FF98FF10771EFEF01554" baseAuthorityName="Grinnell" baseAuthorityYear="1917" box="[163,262,772,793]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Paroreomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="84" pageNumber="84" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E50FF98FF10771EFEF01554" box="[163,262,772,793]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="84">montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because he also listed a ‘‘type’’ of the female, thus not treating a single specimen as the 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E50FF98FEAC7727FE7A151E" box="[287,396,829,851]" pageId="84" pageNumber="84">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A35036B69E50FF98FEB7779BFE3215DB" blockId="84.[260,452,897,918]" box="[260,452,897,918]" pageId="84" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E50FF98FEB7779BFE3215DB" box="[260,452,897,918]" class="Aves" family="Estrildidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="84" pageNumber="84" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">ESTRILDIDAE</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A35036B69E50FF98FFC977AFFE5E1248" blockId="84.[93,619,948,1029]" pageId="84" pageNumber="84">
<bibRefCitation id="C77E4B479E50FF98FFC977AFFE881587" author="Payne, R. B." box="[122,382,948,970]" pageId="84" pageNumber="84" pagination="299 - 377" refId="ref124981" refString="Payne, R. B. 2010. Family Estrildidae (waxbills), species accounts. In J. del Hoyo, A. Elliott, and D. Christie (editors), Handbook of the birds of the world, vol. 15, weavers to New World warblers: 299 - 377. Barcelona: Lynx Edicions, 879 pp., 60 pls., photographs." type="book chapter" year="2010">Payne (2010: 235–248)</bibRefCitation>
has summarized the results of recent mitochondrial and nuclear DNA studies of 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E50FF98FE9177F5FE521248" box="[290,420,1007,1029]" class="Aves" family="Estrildidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="84" pageNumber="84" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Estrildidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
